						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: [Parāntaka I] Year: 21: 928 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Beginning lost. It records that Mūvēndappallavaraiyaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Āditta Piḍāraṉ, son of Vīranārāṇappallavaraiyaṉ, a native of Kūgūr in Vaḍa Paṉaṅgāḍu-nāḍu in Mīkkūṟu (a sub-division) of Chōḷa-nāḍu, made a gift of two Īḻa-lamps and three hundred and sixty sheep to burn two perpetual lamps to the god of Tiruvoṟṟiyūr. He also donated a fly-whisk <hi rend="italic">(chauri)</hi> with a gold handle. </p>						

						</summary>
